<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,332,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is taken from a character of this species (the short cerci); it is composed from the Latin adjective 
<emphasis box="[366,434,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">brevis</emphasis>
(short) plus the noun 
<emphasis box="[680,748,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">cauda</emphasis>
(tail or appendage).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
